item.title: Don't you worry child
item.description: There was a time, I used to look into my father’s eyes In a happy home, I was a king I had a golden throne Those days are gone, now the memories are on the wall I hear the songs from the places where I was born Up on the hill, across the blue lake, That’s where I had my first heartbreak I still remember how it all changed My father said Don’t you worry, don’t you worry child See heaven’s got a plan for you Don’t you worry, don’t you worry now Yeah!
